# Deobfuscated Code & Explanation

## Deobfuscated Version

```javascript
var TAU = 6.283;        // 2π
var PHI = 1.618;        // Golden ratio
var INV_SQRT2 = 0.707;  // 1/√2

var config = {
    combustion: 4000,       // Repulsion strength between nodes
    bookmarkCoeff: 0.004,   // Default spring stiffness
    communication: 0.92,    // Velocity damping/friction
    quarterly: 0.0003,      // Gravity strength toward center
    clientMax: 40,          // Max number of particles
    serverDecay: 0.04,      // Particle velocity decay
    sigma: 0.06             // Lens smoothing factor
};

// "edges" are actually the NODES of the graph (confusing naming)
var edges = [
    { id: 'hub',     label: 'Hub',     r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'alpha',   label: 'Alpha',   r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'beta',    label: 'Beta',    r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'gamma',   label: 'Gamma',   r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'delta',   label: 'Delta',   r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// "nodes" are actually the EDGES/LINKS of the graph
var nodes = [
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub',   b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'gamma',   rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'beta',  b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

var lens  = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };  // Current camera
var focus = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };  // Target camera
var stream = [];  // Array of floating particles
var cycle = 0;

function edgeById(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        if (edges[i].id === id) return edges[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Main physics: repulsion + spring attraction + gravity + damping
function converge() {
    // 1) Node-node REPULSION (Coulomb-like)
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < edges.length; j++) {
            var dx = edges[i].x - edges[j].x;
            var dy = edges[i].y - edges[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.combustion / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            edges[i].vx += fx;
            edges[i].vy += fy;
            edges[j].vx -= fx;
            edges[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2) Spring ATTRACTION along links (Hooke's law)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        var nodeA = edgeById(nodes[i].a);
        var nodeB = edgeById(nodes[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - nodes[i].rest;
        var force = (nodes[i].k || config.bookmarkCoeff) * displacement;
        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3) Gravity toward center (400, 300) + velocity damping + position update
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        edges[i].vx *= config.communication;  // friction
        edges[i].vy *= config.communication;
        edges[i].vx += (400 - edges[i].x) * config.quarterly;  // gravity X
        edges[i].vy += (300 - edges[i].y) * config.quarterly;  // gravity Y
        edges[i].x += edges[i].vx;
        edges[i].y += edges[i].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a particle from a random node
function emitStream() {
    if (stream.length >= config.clientMax) return;
    var source = edges[Math.floor(Math.random() * edges.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * INV_SQRT2;
    stream.push({
        x: source.x,
        y: source.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * PHI * INV_SQRT2
    });
}

// Update and age particles, remove expired ones
function decayStream() {
    for (var i = stream.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = stream[i];
        p.age++;
        p.vx *= (1 - config.serverDecay * 0.125);
        p.vy *= (1 - config.serverDecay * 0.125);
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) stream.splice(i, 1);
    }
}

// Smoothly interpolate camera toward target
function adjustLens() {
    lens.x += (focus.x - lens.x) * config.sigma;
    lens.y += (focus.y - lens.y) * config.sigma;
    lens.zoom += (focus.zoom - lens.zoom) * config.sigma;
}

// Main loop tick
function pulse() {
    converge();
    decayStream();
    adjustLens();
    if (cycle % 3 === 0) emitStream();  // emit particle every 3rd frame
    cycle++;
}

setInterval(pulse, 16);  // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph layout engine with particle effects**. Specifically:

### 🕸️ Graph Simulation
- **6 nodes** (Hub, Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon) connected by **8 spring links**
- Uses classic **force-directed layout** physics:
  - **Repulsion**: All nodes push each other apart (inverse-square law, like electric charges)
  - **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled together via Hooke's law toward a rest length
  - **Gravity**: Gentle pull toward the center point (400, 300)
  - **Damping**: 8% velocity loss per frame to prevent oscillation

### ✨ Particle System
- Every 3 frames, a particle spawns from a random node
- Particles drift outward with random velocity, slowly decaying
- Max 40 particles at once; each lives 800–2000 frames before being removed

### 📷 Camera/Lens
- A smoothly-interpolated virtual camera (`lens`) that eases toward a target (`focus`) using linear interpolation at 6% per frame

### 🔒 Obfuscation Techniques Used
- **String array rotation** with integrity check (the IIFE at the top)
- **RC4 decryption** of string literals (the `a0_0x13b7` function)
- **Control flow flattening** via `switch` on split strings like `'2|7|4|8|0|1|5|6|9|3'.split('|')`
- **Misleading variable names** (`edges` = nodes, `nodes` = links, `combustion` = repulsion force, `communication` = damping)

This is purely a **simulation/animation engine** — there's no rendering code here, suggesting a separate draw loop reads `edges`, `stream`, and `lens` to render the visualization on a canvas.
